## Tech Stack & Context

- This repo is a **Next.js 14** app using the **App Router** under `src/app`.
- All application code is written in **TypeScript** (`.ts`, `.tsx`).
- Styling is primarily via **Tailwind CSS** and project-level design system components in `packages/ui`.

## General Guidelines

- Prefer **small, focused React function components**; avoid class components.
- Keep components **presentational** when possible and move data/loading logic into hooks or lib utilities.
- Use **TypeScript types/interfaces** for component props and external data; avoid `any`.
- Keep shared types and UI primitives in `packages/interface` and `packages/ui` where appropriate.

## Data & API Usage

- When calling APIs or GraphQL endpoints, centralize clients and queries in `src/lib` (or an appropriate package) instead of in components.
- Handle errors explicitly and surface user-friendly messages; avoid silent failures.

## Styling & Layout

- Use **Tailwind utility classes** for most styling, with higher-level components from `packages/ui` for repeated patterns.
- Prefer composable layout components (e.g., shells, sections) over deeply nested ad-hoc markup.

## Tooling & Workflow

- Keep code formatted with `npm run format` / `npm run format-check` (Prettier).
- Keep code passing `npm run lint` (Next.js + ESLint config in this repo).
- When adding dependencies, prefer existing libraries already used in the project.

